summary: After receiving many compliments about my Skyrim screen captures, I decided to share the experience. I have spent countless hours tweaking my ENB configuration files, testing and checking thousands of settings. I believe using these files will save you a lot of work. I hope it gives you much pleasure.
descriptionHtml:
[center]

[size=5][b][color=#ff0000]JW's High Quality ENB Preset[/color][/b][/size][/center]


I have spent many hours fine tuning hundreds of settings in the  ENB  file over the course of several months. This file will save you time doing making those save adjustments. This preset should be used with my other files for the best results. The quality will leave you amazed. If you experience a large drop in your frame rate, you can manually adjust these files by simply lowering the values that affect your video card and resolution.

More than 800 lines of ENB configurations have been set by me over a period of many weeks. I have meticulously tested almost every line in these files. This process took more than 10,000 adjustments. You may still have to make adjustments to meet the needs of your computer.

This file is best used with my[b] Skyrim ENB[/b] Guide.

*** [color=#ffff00][b]INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS[/b][/color]
      Extract the files and drop them into your main Skyrim Folder. Keep this file ready on hand, because you will need this when your Skyrim bugs out on you. When that happens, just extract and copy them over into that same folder again.
Backup your current enbseries.ini and enblocal.ini files just in case your computer cannot handle the stress of being a HIGH QUALITY ENB.

     INI File locations are:
1. [b]Windows 7 and Windows Vista[/b]:  [size=2]C:\Users\USERNAME\Documents\My Games\Skyrim[/size]
2. [b]Windows XP:   C:\Documents and Settings\USERNAME\Documents\My Games\Skyrim
[/b]


***[color=#ffff00][b] OPTIONAL FILES[/b][/color]
I have been saving variations of my ENB configurations for use whenever I want to revert to a previous setting. Although each package produces a different appearance, depending on the time of day, as well as the place, each package is dated, and each date is an indicator of the level of my experience at the time I created the file. Hence, I am more experience now than when I began. Try these, and see which one suits your tastes.


 [i]   ENJOY![/i]
